protected_spaces_details.description: Provision for children and young people

description: Demolition of existing buildings and construction of 1,102 dwellings (an increase of 119 residential units over and above the 2013 consent figure of 983 dwellings) (Use Class C3) together with 2,110m2 retail/commercial (Use Class A1-A5/D1), 1,004m2 retail/commercial (Use Class A2-A5), 370m2 restaurant, 2,629m2 community (Use Class D1), 949m2 supermarket (Use Class A1), 772m2 leisure (Use Class D2), a public square, publicly accessible open space and associated access, servicing, car parking, cycle parking and landscaping as a minor material amendment under S.73 to vary conditions 1, 7 and 8 of the planning permission granted on the 27th March 2015 (14/2607/F), in order to allow changes to the layout, elevations and height of Blocks C and D, rconfiguration of the combined Phase 3 basement level, alterations to the road network around Blocks C, D and E, and a revision to the Kidbrooke Village Centre Play Strategy.
